+# IC Workspace Seed Provider Comparison
+
+Comparison smoke for GitHub issues #67 and #68. Default scope: seed provider → candidate workspace → identity/evidence → key file existence. Full validation/runtime path is optional and was not required for this decision.
+
+## Providers compared
+
+| Dimension | LocalPathProvider | BuckBackendDescriptorProvider |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| provider | `local_path` | `buck_descriptor` |
+| implementation complexity | Low: copy tree from declared source path | Medium: parse descriptor JSON, resolve Buck label metadata |
+| LOC / new concepts | Materializer + exclude list + digest | Descriptor schema + validation + optional `buck2 build` |
+| runtime overhead | One filesystem copy per candidate | Descriptor load (+ optional Buck build); same copy path for Level 2 |
+| debuggability | High: paths are plain directories | Medium: indirection through descriptor file / target |
+| failure modes | Missing source, copy I/O | Malformed descriptor, `repo_checks` leakage, Buck unavailable |
+| candidate workspace purity | Copy excludes `.git`, caches, `buck-out`, `repomix-output.xml` | Same (Level 2 uses `local_path` seed) |
+| evidence identity quality | `source` = absolute path; `sha256` = tree digest | `source` = Buck label; `sha256` = same tree digest when path matches |
+| agent / meta-harness legibility | Easiest to explain | Better for repo-graph-addressable backends |
+| public user ergonomics | Works without Buck | Requires descriptor convention or committed JSON |
+| future Git/archive support | Add new seed kinds + providers | Descriptor can point at archive/git without changing materializer |
+| recommendation | **Sufficient for now** | **Worth adopting internally**; not required for all users yet |
+
+## Decision (#68)
+
+1. **Is LocalPathProvider sufficient for now?** Yes. It satisfies the lifecycle invariant (validated workspace = launched workspace) with minimal moving parts.
+2. **Is BuckBackendDescriptorProvider worth adopting now?** Yes for repo-internal wiring (`//src/iterative-context:optimizable_backend`). Public configs can stay `local_path` until bundle wiring (#66) lands.
+3. **Archive snapshots:** **Deferred.** Level 2 `local_path` descriptor is enough for comparison; no archive field required.
+4. **Follow-up issue sequence:** #63 candidate validation → #64 runtime launch → #66 config/provider wiring; keep repo checks on `//:check` / `//src/iterative-context:check*`, never in descriptors.
+5. **Basis for next wave:** Merge `sb-ic-62-localpath-provider` + `sb-ic-65-buck-descriptor-provider` into integration; default provider for inner loops remains `local_path`.
+
+## Evidence
+
+- Go smoke: `internal/adapters/workspace/compare/compare_test.go` (`TestProviderComparisonSmoke`)
+- Both providers produce `WorkspaceSeed` → `ICCandidateWorkspace` with `pyproject.toml`, `server.py`, `validate_policy.py`, and `tests/` present.
